      "content": "While better lifestyle habits can sometimes influence drug metabolism, you cannot safely test a lower dose without professional guidance. Trying to cut your dose unilaterally carries a real risk of insufficient anticoagulation, which could lead to dangerous clot formation. For a straight answer, the risk of inadequate protection outweighs the perceived benefit of saving a pill. You must discuss any dosage change with your cardiologist or hematologist.",
      "source": "target",
